    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "You use the shared instance of this object by assigning it to the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/quartzcore/calayer/1410749-layoutmanager"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " property of any layer objects to which you have added constraints. During a layout update, Core Animation uses the layout manager to update the size and position of the sublayers based on the registered set of constraints."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Constraints let you define a set of geometric relationships between a layer and its sibling layers or between a layer and its superlayer. These relationships are expressed using constraint objects, which are instances of the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/quartzcore/caconstraint"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " class. When creating constraints, you can reference a layer by name using that objectâ€™s "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/quartzcore/calayer/1410879-name"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " property. You can also use the special name "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "superlayer"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " to refer to the layer's superlayer."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "aside",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "It is possible to specify a set of constraints that will cause layout to fail. For example, layout may fail if your constraints contain a circular dependency. When that happens, the behavior of the layout manager is undefined."
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "style": "important"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "This class is not meant to be subclassed.  "
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
